The paper presents new algorithms for inverse reinforcement learning (IRL) in convex optimization settings. This topic is closely related to machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), robotics (cs.RO), control systems (cs.SY), and mathematical optimization (cs.MA). The use of Gaussian process models and preference graphs also suggests a connection to probabilistic methods (cs.AI, cs.LG). Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.SY, and cs.MA.
